President Obama has proclaimed May 9, 2014, as Military Spouse Appreciation Day. In his proclamation, he recognizes the strength, loyalty, and commitment of military spouses and the sacrifices they make. The administration is working to support military families through various initiatives, such as helping them avoid foreclosure, investing in their education, and providing childcare and career training. The Joining Forces initiative, led by First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden, aims to expand employment opportunities for veterans and their spouses. The President emphasizes the importance of honoring military spouses and providing support to their families.